nginx proxy process 
1. In this process we can access the application without load balancer and without exposing port number.

2. create public server and deploy application in private server 

3. Install nginx in public server --> sudo yum install nginx -y --> systemctl start nginx

4. change the configuration file of nginx  --> vi /etc/nginx/conf.d/flaskapp.conf

5. Add this file
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name 98.81.160.29;  # add public ip

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:5000;     # add private ip of server where application is running
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }
}


6. systemctl restart nginx 

7. Take the public ip and access the application without load balancer and without exposing port number.




